The paper introduces a novel text representation that preserves the 2D layout of a document and presents a generic document understanding pipeline for structured documents. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper makes use of a fully convolutional encoder-decoder network, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG) research. Finally, the paper demonstrates its capabilities on an information extraction task, which is a common application of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) research.
